   BBA-BLUEJAYS-GREEN (Toronto) _ When Jim Fregosi, longtime
baseball man and current manager of the Toronto Blue Jays, was
asked to compare his 26-year-old right fielder, Shawn Green, to
players of the past or present, he started with a contemporary
all-star and ended with a legend. ''I think about Larry Walker at
Colorado and Dave Parker, who used to play right field for
Pittsburgh,'' said Fregosi, who has been active in the major
leagues as a player, manager or executive since 1961. ``Those guys
were complete players. You can even go back to Roberto Clemente, a
guy that could run and throw, hit for average, hit for power and
drive in runs.'' By Chris Broussard.
