<P>
   FDA-WATCHDOG (Seattle) _ After investing nearly two-thirds of
his life safeguarding foods and drugs for the American public,
Roger Lowell plans to bicycle across the nation, celebrate his
successes and perhaps forget about what still troubles him. ``We're
doing a good job protecting your health and safety but we're not
protecting your pocketbook anymore,'' Lowell said. A
straight-shooter equally respected within the agency as well as by
many in the industries he has regulated, the FDA's top local
watchdog retired from his post Friday.
</P>
<P>
   By Tom Paulson. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
