Ourselves Alone: The Story of Elizabeth Cady Stanton &AMP; Susan B.
Anthony.'' With the finger-wagging zeal of a televangelist, Burns
told TV critics Saturday that Stanton and Anthony, pioneers of the
women's movement, are the two most important females in the
American experience, but most Americans know nothing about them.
