<SLUG> BC-FBN-PARCELLS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PARCELLS READY TO DISCUSS FUTURE WITH ANY POTENTIAL OWNER 
</HEADLINE>
 (ms) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. _ Although Bill Parcells has never disclosed how
long he plans to coach the New York Jets, he said Sunday that he
would be willing to discuss his future with any potential owner.
</P>
<P>
   Goldman, Sachs has already prepared a prospectus on the team for
potential buyers. A leading figure in arranging the sale will be
the Jets' president, Steve Gutman, who could oversee a $500 million
deal.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've told Steve Gutman, bring anybody by that you want,''
Parcells said. ``I'll be glad to talk to them.''
</P>
<P>
   Parcells is in the third year of a six-year contract that calls
for him to coach the Jets for at least four seasons. He is also the
team's chief football operations officer and commands an average
salary of $2.4 million a year. He will be 58 later this month.
</P>
<P>
   Parcells has said there will be no front-office changes this
season, and Gutman added that the Jets operate just as they always
have, although he reports to the executors of the will of the late
Leon Hess. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
