<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Monday,
August 2. If you have any questions, please call The Star's News
Desk at (816) 234-4720.
</P>
<P>
   GAMBLE (Washington) _ Contributions from the gambling industry
to federal election campaigns grew by 400 percent from 1992 to
1998, a rate 10 times that of political contributions overall, a
new congressional audit says. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The General Accounting Office said donations grew from $1.1
million to $5.7 million during a time of rapid gambling expansion
and deepening concern that Congress would further regulate and tax
the industry. By Kevin Murphy. Story will move in the ``a''
category.
</P>
<P>
   ROCKET (Argonia, Kan.) _ About the time most people are clocking
in at work or finishing up the newspaper at home this morning,
Bruce Lee will help escort a rocket he built to a specially made
launch pad. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   He'll be among the last of at least 300 adults since Thursday
who have made the trek from as far away as Australia to this patch
of Kansas about 30 miles south of Wichita. They came to take part
in a shoot of ``Large and Dangerous Rocket Ships,'' otherwise known
as the annual Tripoli International High-Power Rocket Launch, the
largest and most prestigious annual event of its kind. &QL; 
By Matthew Schofield. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
</TEXT>
